A photorealistic close-up of a vintage mechanical switchboard with multiple brass levers and colored cables, where each lever connects to a different glowing pathway representing parallel processes. The scene is lit by warm amber light filtering through industrial windows, casting long shadows across worn wooden workbenches covered with precision tools and copper components. Steam wisps curl through the air, suggesting active machinery. The switchboard shows intricate engraved numbers and connection points, with some pathways illuminated in cool blue and others in warm orange, symbolizing different versions running simultaneously through the same complex system.
